<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-13T11:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-13T11:36:00-05:00" n="1046" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1046">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9181.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-13T10:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 13, 1913—10 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>548. Department’s October 12, midnight. General Huerta last night said
                            that no violence whatsoever would be done to the deputies but that they
                            must in many cases stand trial for sedition and treason. He requested me
                            to assure my Government that they would be tried fairly by the civil
                            courts.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson O’Shaughnessy</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>